The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, Dec. 28: Private telecom operators have offered security agencies access to their 3G mobile services within six months of launch. Home secretary Gopal K. Pillai and R. Chandrashekhar, secretary in the department of telecommunications, discussed the issue yesterday and are likely to accept the proposal of the operators, official sources said here today.                             
	 New Delhi, Dec. 28: Pratip Chaudhuri, deputy managing director and group executive (international banking) of the State Bank of India, is understood to be leading the race for the post of chairman in the countrys largest lender.                             
	 New Delhi, Dec. 28: Lakshmi N. Mittal and Hindustan Petroleum Corp Ltd plan to sell a 10 per cent stake each in the under-construction Bathinda Refinery in a public offering in the fourth quarter of 2011 to raise Rs 1,000-1,500 crore.                            
	 New Delhi, Dec. 28: The Insurance Regulatory and Development Authority (Irda) today gave its second-stage approval to joint ventures of Religare and the Union Bank for their health insurance venture and Edelweiss-Tokio for life insurance business.
                                                                                                                          
